Class RadarView

java.lang.Object
  View
      edu.bonn.cs.wmp.awarenesswidgets.RadarView
All Implemented Interfaces:
WMPAwarenessWidget
public class RadarView
extends View
implements WMPAwarenessWidget

This Awareness Widget shows the complete currently edited document. It reacts on LineChanges from the corresponding WMPEditText. Addititonally this view displays the current viewports of all session takers. Changes to these are indicated by ViewportChanges - and here is the point where these changes get processed. Keep in mind, that these view is really flexible in it's layout. You may hide it in a slider or display it directly visible on the screen. Any size is allowed.

Author:
Sven Bendel

isInterestedIn

public boolean isInterestedIn(Class<? extends ContentChange> changeClass)
Description copied from interface: WMPAwarenessWidget
This method is called by the subject view of this Awareness Widget when its content changes, but before the ContentChange is propagated to the Awareness Widget. We may decide if we want to get informed about this particular ContentChange by returning true or false.
